          <msContents>
            <summary>Praise (stotra), worship, and veneration of various places around the pilgrimage city of Kāśī (Vārāṇasī), such as Viśveśvara, a form of the Hindu deity Śiva. Presented as a discourse between the Indian sage Nārada and king Yudhiṣṭira. Attributed to the Padmapurāṇa, but no section or chapter given.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
